@vcitizen: CRF, aka Constant ratefactor, is a type of encoding in the x264 -encoder that renders the whole movie in the same quality, 18 in this case. The smaller the number is, the better the quality will be. 18-19 usually produces very nice quality while still maintaining a nice and small file size.
